## Refactoring Protocol

### Pre-Refactor Checks
1. Read CODEBASE_PROFILE.md for existing conventions
2. Identify protected symbols (§4) — do NOT change these
3. Load existing test suite — ensure tests pass before starting

### Scope Declaration (before ANY change)
```
[SCOPE DECLARATION]
Modify O: (files, functions, classes, line ranges)
Modify X: (with reasons — e.g. "referenced by 7 modules")
Must preserve: (symbols, API contracts, global state)
```

### Scope Discipline
|Scenario|Forbidden|Allowed|
|------|------|------|
|Naming refactor|Logic changes|Rename only, update all references|
|Structure refactor|API signature changes|Internal reorganization|
|Extract method/class|Behavior changes|Move code, preserve behavior|
|Remove dead code|Removing used code|Only verified unused code|

### Refactoring Principles
1. SOLID: Single Responsibility, Open/Closed, Liskov, Interface Segregation, Dependency Inversion
2. Composition over inheritance
3. Dependency Injection for testability
4. Interface segregation, implementation deferred until needed
5. YAGNI: only abstract when pain is felt, not before

### Self-Verification (after refactor)
```
□ All existing tests still pass?
□ Protected symbols unchanged?
□ No behavior changes introduced?
□ Naming conventions consistent with CODEBASE_PROFILE §3?
□ Imports organized (no unused, no wildcard)?
□ No new dependencies added without approval?
```

### Refactoring Report
```
[REFACTOR SUMMARY]
Completed:
  - (change 1): (file:scope) — (what was done + why)
Preserved:
  - (symbols intentionally left unchanged + reasons)
Test Results:
  - All N tests passing / N failures (list)
Warnings:
  - (if any)
```
